Assignment: Ansible
1. create two ec2 instances
2. configure one server as a ansible master and one as a ansible client
3. create inventory file and keep client private IP inside of that file.
4. test the connectivity by using ansible ansible -m ping all -I <inventory file>
6. configure your target as a Jenkins server using ansible (java pkg name java-21-amazon-corretto)

tasks:
  - name: java install
    yum:
      name: java-21-amazon-corretto
      state: present
  - name: add jenkins repo
    ansible.builtin.command: sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo \
    https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo |sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key
  - name: install jenkins
    yum:
      name: jenkins
      state: present
  - name: start jenkins service
    service:
      name: jenkins
      state: started
